          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Pale brown silty loam (medial, typic). Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.alfisol.fragiboralf.coarse.86P1994.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Dark grayish brown and very dark brown extremely stoney coarse sandy loam (loamy skeletal, mixed, pergelic). Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.inceptisol.cryumbrept.coarse.87P3855.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "The parent material is schist and phyllite. Dark yellowish brown micaceous loam (coarse-loamy, micaceous, mesic typic), from piedmonts. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.inceptisol.dystrochrept.coarse.88P2535.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Brown sandy loam (coarse-loamy over sandy-skeletal, mixed, mesic fluventic). 4.85% organic carbon, 9.9% clay, 14.2% silt, 75.9% sand. Clay mineralogy: small mica peakand weak vermiculite, kaolinite, and goethite peaks. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.inceptisol.haplumbrept.coarse.88P4699.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Parent material is loess from mixed material. Dark grayish brown silty loam, (fine, montmorillonitic, mesic xeric). Physiography: upland slope in plateaus or tablelands. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.mollisol.agialboll.coarse.85P5339.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Gray silty clay, (fine, montmorillonitic, mesic cumulic). Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.mollisol.haplaquoll.coarse.86P4603.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "Parent material: volcanic ash from acidic-ash material over glacial till from mixed-igneous and metamorphic matter. Physiography: hillside with 18 east-facing slope. Dark reddish brown, organic-rich, silty loam (A0 horizon), (medial over loamy, mixed typic). Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.soil.spodosol.cryohumod.coarse.87P4264.spectrum.txt"
          }
        ]
